Yes, we can use machine learning algorithms such as logistic regression or support vector machines to classify the sentences as positive or negative. To do this, we need to extract relevant features from the text data. Some common features used in sentiment analysis include:
1. Bag of words: We can create a vocabulary of all the unique words in the dataset and represent each sentence as a vector of word counts.
